                73</ref>) <marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></enactingFormula><commencementNote>[20 August
            1976]<marker role="blank-line"></marker></commencementNote><sourceNote class="align_right">(Format changes—<ref href="/hk/2019/er2">E.R. 2 of
                2019</ref>)</sourceNote><section id="ID_1438402754691_001" name="s1" reason="inEffect" role="rule" startPeriod="2019-06-20" status="operational" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><heading>Citation</heading><content>These rules may be cited as the Practising Certificate (Solicitors) Rules.</content></section><section id="ID_1438402755066_001" name="s2" reason="inEffect" role="rule" startPeriod="2019-06-20" status="operational" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Application for practising certificates</heading><content>An application by a solicitor under <ref>section 6</ref> of the Ordinance for a
            practising certificate shall be in Form 1 in the <ref>Schedule</ref>. </content><sourceNote>(<ref href="/hk/1997/ln311">L.N. 311 of 1997</ref>) </sourceNote></section><section id="ID_1438402755081_002" name="s3" reason="inEffect" role="rule" startPeriod="2022-01-01" status="operational" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Fee for practising certificate</heading><content>When an application for a practising certificate is lodged with the Society, there
            shall at the same time be paid to the Society a fee of $6,500.</content><sourceNote class="align_justified">(<ref href="/hk/1983/ln344">L.N. 344 of 1983</ref>; <ref href="/hk/1986/ln259">L.N. 259 of 1986</ref>; <ref href="/hk/1987/ln341">L.N. 341 of
